or (<b>12</b>) is formed in a concave surface which satisfies a following conditional expression (1): L/1.2&#x3c;R&#x3c;1.5L - - - (1), where R denotes the absolute value of the radius of curvature of the center portion of the auxiliary mirror (<b>12</b>) which corresponds to the non-transmitting portion (<b>12</b><i>f</i>), and L denotes a distance from the intermediate image forming position to the center portion of the auxiliary mirror which corresponds to the non-transmitting portion.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>